    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/2604.13145v1</id>
    <title>Secular Brightness Trends of Starlink and OneWeb Satellites</title>
    <updated>2026-04-14T16:09:35Z</updated>
    <link href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.13145v1" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/>
    <link href="https://arxiv.org/pdf/2604.13145v1" rel="related" type="application/pdf" title="pdf"/>
    <summary>Magnitudes recorded from 2021 through 2026 for Starlink VisorSats reveal brightening of 0.6 magnitudes, while those of OneWeb show dimming of 0.4. Both trends are significant at 3 sigma. This study is based on 1.6 million magnitudes recorded by the MMT9 robotic observatory.</summary>
